name: Density
description: Starting metropolitan area density of 4000 person per square mile. Approximately the density of Portland urbanized area.

name: Congestn
description: Approximate Portland metropolitan congestion. 68% of freeway and arterial lane miles are congested during the peak period.

name: AutoComf
description: Assumed proportion in the Portland metropolitan area where travel is in conditions where driving requires a low level of focus.

name: AutoSpd
description: Ratio between average peak period and off-peak speed on freeways and arterials in Portland metropolitan area.

name: AutoMPG
description: Assumed average MPG for all light-duty vehicles.

name: MoblTech
description: Assume 50 percent of travelers have smart phones.

name: DRTransit
description: Assume that 5% of travelers have access to demand-responsive transportation with relatively short wait times.

name: FRTransit
description: Assume 5% of travelers have access to fixed route transit with relatively short wait times.

name: TransitAccess
description: Assume 5% of travelers have a transit stop within 1/4 mile.

name: LWElecVeh
description: Almost no travelers have electric bicycles or similar.

name: LowSpdInf
description: Assume that 20% of travelers can get to a variety of destinations using low traffic stress routes.
